GENERIC GAME RECORD TEMPLATE
790.15 — Game Theory / Formal Game Models / Strategic Interaction
========================================================
# Summary

This file is a template and reference guide for 
recording game data in a standardized format. It 
defines a structured schema (`GAME_RECORD Γ`) for 
capturing complete information about any game, 
including:

- Players
: ID, name, stats, and action history

- State Space
: Game states with mode (sequential or simultaneous), 
  active players, and history

- Action Log
: Timestamped player moves tied to specific states

- Random Log
: Stochastic events (coin flips, dice rolls, etc.) 
  with outcomes

- Transition Log
: State changes triggered by actions or random events

- Terminal Outcome
: Final state and payoffs (utilities) for each player

- Equivalence Metadata (optional)
: Canonical forms and transformations for comparing 
  structurally similar games

The template is designed to be **game-agnostic**—it works 
for any game type (board games, card games, probability 
games like Penney's Game, etc.).

The file cites a 2020 IEEE conference paper on formal 
game grammars and equivalence, indicating this schema 
is grounded in formal game theory research for 
normalizing and comparing game records systematically.

GAME_RECORD Γ
========================================================

GAME_ID: <unique identifier>
GAME_NAME: <string>
VERSION: <string>

PLAYERS
--------------------------------------------------------
P := { p1, p2, ..., pn }

For each player pi:
    pi.ID        : <string>
    pi.Name      : <string>
    pi.Stats     : <key-value map>
    pi.Actions   : <list of action entries>

STATE_SPACE
--------------------------------------------------------
State s ∈ S:
    s.ID         : <string>
    s.Mode       : SEQ | SIM
    s.Active     : { players }
    s.Info       : <snapshot>
    s.History    : <list of transition IDs>

Initial State:
    s0.ID        : <string>

ACTION_LOG
--------------------------------------------------------
Action entry α_k:
    α_k.ID       : <string>
    α_k.State    : <state ID>
    α_k.Profile  : { (pi : ai) }
    α_k.Timestamp: <time>

RANDOM_LOG
--------------------------------------------------------
Random event r_k:
    r_k.ID       : <string>
    r_k.State    : <state ID>
    r_k.Dist     : <distribution>
    r_k.Outcome  : <value>
    r_k.Timestamp: <time>

TRANSITION_LOG
--------------------------------------------------------
Transition τ_k:
    τ_k.ID       : <string>
    τ_k.From     : <state ID>
    τ_k.Input    : <action ID or random ID>
    τ_k.To       : <state ID>
    τ_k.Timestamp: <time>

TERMINAL_OUTCOME
--------------------------------------------------------
Terminal state s_T:
    s_T.ID       : <string>
    s_T.Info     : <snapshot>

Outcome ω:
    ω.Utilities  : { (pi : U(pi)) }
    ω.Metadata   : <optional>

EQUIVALENCE_METADATA (optional)
--------------------------------------------------------
Canonical_Form   : <normalized tree ID>
Transformations  : <list of applied equivalence ops>
Distance_Vector  : <metrics>

